.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH task 1  "task " 
.SH NAME
task \- Task management
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtask\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Task management
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
task\-list(1)
List tasks
.TP
task\-show(1)
Show task details
.TP
task\-create(1)
Create a task
.TP
task\-convert\-session(1)
Convert an existing chat session into a task
.TP
task\-update(1)
Update a task
.TP
task\-delete(1)
Delete a task
.TP
task\-control(1)
Control a task (start, pause, resume, stop, run_now)
.TP
task\-progress(1)
Show task progress
.TP
task\-run\-log(1)
Inspect persisted per\-run event logs for a task
.TP
task\-send(1)
Send a message to a running task
.TP
task\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
